You can use a simple regex to parse your filename and capture the text you want into two groups and use them the way you want. This Java code should help. And the way this works is, the regex first captures everything before `@` (using `(.*)`) excluding any whitespace before that and second part is captured starting from `@` followed by one or more any character other than a dot using `(@[^.]+)`

	String s = &quot;Beach Video @instagram.mp4&quot;;
	Pattern p = Pattern.compile(&quot;(.*)\\s*(@[^.]+).*&quot;);
	Matcher m = p.matcher(s);
	if (m.matches()) {
		System.out.println(&quot;First part: &quot; + m.group(1));
		System.out.println(&quot;Second part: Source &quot; + m.group(2));
	} else {
		System.out.println(&quot;Unexpected file format&quot;);
	}

